---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import InnerPageHero from "../components/InnerPageHero.astro";
import { heroImages } from "../data/wixImages";
import { fairmontAwardsUrl } from "../data/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Golf Course"
  description="Stanley Thompson's Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge — Canada's #1 golf resort course in Jasper National Park."
>
  <InnerPageHero eyebrow="The course" title="Canada's #1 Golf Resort Course" image={heroImages.course} />
  <div class="page-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Every hole at Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge provides its own unique views and challenges. Stanley Thompson, Canada&apos;s master golf course architect, displayed
      some of the finest work of his career with this design: elevated tee boxes, dramatic bunkering, and holes aligned with distant mountain vistas.
    </p>
    <p>
      Highly acclaimed for its challenging layout and spectacular beauty, the club is rated by <em>SCOREGolf</em> as the #1 Golf Resort Course in Canada. Most
      recently, <em>SCOREGolf</em> ranked Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge Golf Club #2 among Canada&apos;s public courses (2021). Few courses in the world match the
      rugged majesty of this national treasure, nestled between sparkling lakes, pristine forest, and rocky peaks.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each round takes you on an exquisite journey through a stunning mountain backdrop. Wildlife abounds — from deer, elk, and Canada geese to the occasional
      curious bear: a true Rocky Mountain mulligan.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="callout">
      <p>
        <strong>&ldquo;Definite &lsquo;Bucket List&rsquo; Course!&rdquo;</strong> — An unexpected opportunity for 9 memorable holes at the #1 rated resort course
        in Canada. Staff were exceptionally helpful and a brand new set of TaylorMade hire clubs were the icing on the cake.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0"><em>TripAdvisor, Peter J313</em></p>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Awards &amp; accolades</h2>
    <p>
      The Stanley Thompson designed mountain course has earned prestigious recognition across Canada and the world — including <em>SCOREGolf</em>,{" "}
      <em>Golf Digest</em>, and <em>Canadian Golf Magazine</em>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Ranked #3 — <em>SCOREGolf</em> Best Golf Courses in Canada, 2022</li>
      <li>Ranked #2 — <em>SCOREGolf</em> Top 59 Canadian Public Golf Courses, 2021</li>
      <li>Ranked #58 — <em>Golf Digest</em> World Top 100 Golf Courses, 2020</li>
      <li>Ranked #1 Most Beautiful Golf Course in Canada — <em>SCOREGolf</em>, 2018</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <a href={fairmontAwardsUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">See the full list of awards and accolades</a> on Fairmont.com.
    </p>

    <h2>Scorecard &amp; tips</h2>
    <p>
      Each hole offers its own challenges; the course is forgiving and challenging at once. The course rating is maintained by Alberta Golf biannually. Yardage
      Guides are available for purchase in the Golf Shop, with relevant yardages and tips to navigate each hole.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
